Sentencas: Influence of the ohmic contact resistance at the interface between Gd-doped CeO2 (GDC) interlayer and scandia-stabilized zirconia (ScSZ) electrolyte on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) was investigated.
Titulo: Reduction in ohmic contact resistance at interface between Gd-doped CeO2 interlayer and Sc2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte in SOFCs to improve performance

Sentencas: When GDC interlayer was used, the ohmic resistance of SOFCs was increased due to insufficient contact conditions between the GDC interlayer and ScSZ electrolyte.
Titulo: Reduction in ohmic contact resistance at interface between Gd-doped CeO2 interlayer and Sc2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte in SOFCs to improve performance

Sentencas: To improve the contact conditions, the effect of sintering temperature and sintering aids (Mn, Fe, Bi) on the ohmic contact resistance was evaluated.
Titulo: Reduction in ohmic contact resistance at interface between Gd-doped CeO2 interlayer and Sc2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte in SOFCs to improve performance

Sentencas: As a result, using an optimized Mn-modified GDC interlayer (with added 0.3 mol% Mn and sintered at 1300 degrees C) to decrease the ohmic contact resistance, an anode-supported cell with Sr-doped LaFeO3 cathode and ScSZ electrolyte achieved a power density of 1.5 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
